The paper discusses optimization in genetic algorithms, which is a subfield of Evolutionary Computation and Artificial Intelligence. The paper also mentions the MAX-3SAT and Sherrington Kirkpatrick Spin Glasses problems, which are commonly studied in the subfields of Discrete Mathematics and Data Structures. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
